title: Accession Numbers
publication_title: The Lithographs of James McNeill Whistler: The Digital Edition
content:
<section class="osci-tk-epub-section body" id="body">The following list provides accession numbers for the following collections: in Chicago, for the Art Institute of Chicago (AIC), the Mansfield-Whittemore-Crown collection (MWC), and the A. Steven Crown collection (SC); in London, for the British Museum (BM) and the Victoria & Albert Museum (V&A); in Washington, D.C., for the Freer Gallery of Art (FGA) and the National Gallery of Art (NGA). It should be noted that impressions from the Estate of Pauline K. Palmer, housed at The Art Institute of Chicago, do not have accession numbers; nor do the lithographs at the Library of Congress, Washington, D.C., or the Hunterian Art Gallery, University of Glasgow (HAG). However, the Hunterian does distinguish the lithographs that were part of Rosalind Birnie Philip’s gift of 1935 from the other prints in its collection; objects in the Birnie Philip Gift cannot be lent and are designated below with the abbreviation BPI.

The accession numbers are given in the order in which impressions are listed in the entries. When the abbreviation BPI appears, it should be assumed that the first impression listed after HAG in the descriptions of individual impressions is the one from the Birnie Philip Gift.
